The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 October is 80,242 (9,248.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 October, there were 2,434 new confirmed cases (280.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 September, there were 2,528 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (94 fewer cases).
